Y’all get into it. 

I had the opportunity to join an incredible group of Latinx creators exploring the future of identity and culture in the metaverse! My mind was soo blown going through @itsCOVL’s custom “Nuevo Norte” VR installation in Horizon Worlds which explores her take on Tercera Cultura – which had an epic discoteca and the cutest cafecito that felt like home! My wheels are turning on how to bring Fashion and Entertainment into these types of immersive spaces as we all get our heads around what the metaverse is, and can be for us in the future. The goal of the #MetaverseCultureSeries is to create more access for diverse communities into the future of tech, so it was an honor to have a seat at the virtual table as the metaverse is still being shaped. Check out our docushort, a candid conversation with mi familia @misssaramora @jveloz @tortiz.29 and @itscovl and more on “Nuevo Norte” (which will also be at #ArtBasel in Miami this week as a mixed reality mural!) @meta

Honey i’m home!
Never, would I ever thought that I would get the opportunity to be in a television musical. No seriously, I would have never imagined. Life sometimes surprises you in so many ways - this being one of them. 

The way these songs are engraved in my mind. 

Episode 6 is out and it’s our musical episode! I hope you enjoyed watching as much as we loved shooting it. It was such a joy filming it, and watching my costars excel in every moment was pure magic. From my sister @rosannyzayas absolutely enchanting voice (Disney. Seriously get on it!) to having @ileosheng @arienne_mandi @jtoboni and I learn choreography to fit into the times was nothing but a dream come true. 

It was quite an experience for me personally because I absolutely love era movies or TV shows (it’s the fashion tbh) so to be a part of the 1960s really was an honor. As you probably noticed my chair is quite different than the one that I personally use today. 
This was on purpose! How can I be a part of a absolutely different part of history and have a super futuristic chair?! A conversation that we had behind the scenes. If I, well my character Maribel were to actually be in the 1960s with a disability how would it look like? So of course with enough time and research, the props team custom built a chair that is similar to one of the first electric wheelchairs ever built!! I mean, if we’re going to do it, the community has to be represented correctly.

Here are a few of behind-the-scenes photos & videos in the mist of the wonderful chaos of creating a musical. It took a village!

don’t blink, cause you might miss the magical moments. 

2022 was extremely tough for me mentally, but I wouldn’t change a single thing about it. I have grown and learned about myself like I’ve never before. 

Live in the details. Live in the moment. 

Extremely thankful and blessed to have my family and chosen family hugging me at all times. Keeping me grounded and protecting me from anything and anyone who may cause me harm. I love you and I’m thankful to have you in my life. 

Excited for the next year! Excited for the new adventures my life will bring me.

We love a starting role! 
Finally get to present to you a trailer of the short film I was a part of. 

World, I present!

Being comfortable in my own skin did not happen overnight. Quite the opposite, it was a long battle and a roller coaster of emotions that took place for years to get to this place. 

I like to imagine that my body is like the most beautiful garden I’ve ever seen. A garden is only beautiful, because you take time to water her, give her as much sun as possible, love every single pedal and leaf, make sure its surroundings aren’t harming the garden, but most importantly believe, believe that one day, you will look at yourself, and be amazed at how beautiful and unique you are, and that in itself is the most beautiful image you’ll see. 

thank you @womenshealthmag for including me in The Body issue in stands May 9th! Yup, it’s gonna be printed so all y’all can get a copy ♥️

The universe always knows. That is how I have explained every moment during this week. 

A film that was brought to my attention before the shut down of the world a couple years ago before I even considered to fully have acting as part of my career. Flash forward to be able to say that out of 8,000 submitted films for @tribeca film festival 86 were picked! We were one of those! My first lead role!

what is meant for you will always be for you. 

Words cannot explain the gratitude I have to each and every person who has come to one of our screenings and have escaped for 15 minutes. All 3 days are SOLD OUT! 😭♥️ thank you 🙏🏽 

I am so proud of every single person who took time and brought this film to life, and every day that goes by only validates how incredibly talented we are, and deserving of multitude of opportunities to display our art. 

celebrate you, you’re your biggest fan. 

I can go on and on but essentially, I just want to say thank you and I absolutely can’t wait till there is many more lead roles with different kinds of representation on screen. I hope that this inspires everyone to go after your wildest dreams, because you truly never know.

A cute compilation of myself, enjoying a very warm day at home. It consist of sometimes drinking tea, reading, taking photos with my camera, eating random things in this case, a lemon from my lemon tree, or watering my backyard. Basically enjoying life in simple moments.

Feel. 
Allow yourself to be present
to cry
laugh. 
Own and be present in it all. 

We all go through these cycles of uncertainty, feeling like the world is crashing down on us, but in those moments that is where life feels more alive.

If I may be completely honest, over the past few months personally speaking my life has been pretty hard, emotionally. Just a few days ago my therapist told me that I am depressed. Which was a very hard thing to hear her say that out loud since I was in denial for so long. The only other time I admitted to myself that I was - was when I was 15. I am 36 now, and I truly thought that I was strong enough not to go into that void. so, although social media land may seem like everyone is having the best time ever, behind closed doors, things may be drastically different. I felt like maybe if somebody’s going through the same thing, know that you’re not alone. 

I know that for certain things will get better, they always do. I feel it. So, even though this post seems like I am reminding you to feel all the feelings I am putting it out to the universe to remind myself the same. 

To be gentler with myself, and to surround myself with love, safe moments, and laughter. Reminding myself to take deep breaths. 

Everything will always work itself out. xx

Listennnnn. my close friends can tell you how bad I’ve tried to be a plant mom. I have killed so many plans that I almost gave up. 

One random day my neighbor got a delivery of plants, which so happened to be from @easyplant. So I did my own research and noticed that unlike other plant companies, their main focus is to help people become plant parents! (specifically people who have a funeral of plants already) Hope was not lost😭 They have a wide range of plants, free shipping, AND you only have to water them once a month. 

Click in my bio to find yourself a self watering plant right now. OHH! also use discount code 10OFFJILLIAN for ten percent off the whole order! Let me know if you did🌷

What a whirlwind of a year!

In all honesty, 2023 brought its fair share of chaos and “what in the world is happening” moments. While I’m eager for a fresh start in the new year, I wanted to take a moment to reflect on the pockets of joy that peppered this rollercoaster ride.

Watching this video alone flooded my heart with warmth, serving as a reminder of the incredible people in my life. Amidst the chaos, I’ve been blessed with the most amazing connections, and I’m eternally grateful for each one of you.

There were moments when the world felt like a lonely place, but I’ve come to realize I was never truly alone. This post is a shoutout to you all, a heartfelt thank you for being my constant companions. It’s a blessing that extends beyond what I can express in a single post.

So, here’s to gratitude! I’m grateful for you, for sticking by me through thick and thin.

Now, I’m curious—what are you grateful for this year? Share your moments of gratitude, and let’s keep this positivity train rolling! 🥰
